<h1>TNPSC Group 1 Exam post, syllabus, question paper</h1> 
  <p>TNPSC  Group 1 exam is administrated by the Tamil Nadu  Public Service Commission (TNPSC). The TNPSC conducts various recruitment exams  for Group I, II, III, IV, and vao vacancies in the Tamil Nadu state.&nbsp;<strong>TNPSC  Group 1 Prelims exams 2021 result is announced</strong>. All the essential particulars  about tnpsc exam are given below:<br>
      <strong>Latest  Update on TNPSC Group 1 Exam 2021</strong> </p>
  <ol start="1" type="1">
    <li>The commission has released       the&nbsp;TNPSC Group 1 Prelims exams result&nbsp;on 9th Feb 2021. Download the list of all students       who have been permitted to the TNPSC Mains exams stage.</li>
    <li>TNPSC Mains exam 2021 to announced       on 28th May, 29th May, and 30th May 2021.</li>
    <li>The TNPSC Prelims exams Admit       Card 2021 for Group 1 have been released. Download the TNPSC Admit Card       Details&nbsp;.</li>
    <li>Important instructions for TNPSC       Group 1 Prelims that is going to take place on 3rd January 2021:</li>
  </ol>
  <ul>
    <ul>
      <li>Candidates have to use  only a black ballpoint pen on the OMR sheets. No various colored-pens are  allowed.</li>
      <li>Candidates will not be  permitted inside the examination hall after 9.15 AM. They will not be allowed  to leave the examination hall before 1.15 PM.</li>
      <li>The exam was conducted  in 32 districts at 856 examination centers.</li>
    </ul>
    <li>The post-wise disintegration  of vacancy for TNPSC Group 1 (Combined Civil Services) Examination 2021 has  been released by tnpsc commission. Download the full details of the vacancy on  the&nbsp;TNPSC Group 1 announcement&nbsp;page at this time.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Before the newest information,  TNPSC had made it compulsory for the students to download their Aadhaar card  numbers at the time of applying for the tnpsc Commission’s exams. Fingerprints  of all students will be verified with the biometric information available using  the Aadhaar card and only then will be they permitted to sit for exams in the hall.<br>
    A listing of&nbsp;all <strong>TNPSC Examinations in 2020 -2021</strong>&nbsp;is given below  followed by that of 2019:</p>
  <ol start="1" type="1">
