  <p><h3>TNPSC Group 1 2021 Eligibility Criteria</h3><br>
    Candidates must check the eligibility criteria before applying  and appearing for the TNPSC Group 1 exam. Tnpsc exam eligibility criteria are  set by the Tamil Nadu Public Service Commission in terms of current academic  qualifications, age limit, physical qualification, etc. The criteria for TNPSC  Group 1 change category-wise. Candidates can check the detailed eligibility criteria  below.<br>
  <h3>Academic Qualification</h3></p>
  <ul>
    <li>The       minimum current academic qualification for TNPSC Group 1 is graduation in       any department i.e. It is necessary for all candidates to at least hold a bachelor’s       degree from any UGC recognized university.</li>
    <li>All       candidates must have acquired the minimum qualification in the order of       the studies as 10th + 12th/HSC + UG Degree or its equivalent + UG Degree       from any UGC recognized University/Institutions.</li>
    <li>It       is necessary for all candidates applying for the TNPSC Group 1 exam to       have sufficient knowledge of Tamil medium.</li>
    <li>All       aspirands who appear for their last exam are also allowable to show for       the TNPSC Group 1 Exam under terms and conditions that they must obtain proof       of passed the degree exam at the time of upload the credentials for the TNPSC       Group 1 Mains Exam. deteriorating the exam, the candidate will not be       allowed for the TNPSC Group 1 2021 Mains examination.</li>
    <li>The       candidates who cleared their final exam of MBBS or any Medical Exam, but       have not finished their internship are granted to appear for the TNPSC       Group 1 Preliminary Exam 2021.</li>
    <li>The       candidates who are applying for the posts of Deputy Superintendent of       Police (DSP) and District Officers (Fire and Rescue Services) certain       physical qualifications that can be checked on the official notification       link.</li>
  </ul>
  <p><h3>Age Limit</h3></p>
