  <h3>TNPSC Group 1 2021 Application Process</h3><br>
    students aspiring to mark the TNPSC Group 1 examination should inclusive  the submission procedure before the time limit. The hall ticket will be issued  only to those applications are eligible who have registered and paid the  application fee correctly. The first step is to require One-Time  Registration(OTR) of the candidate and the second step is to fill the  application online on time.<br>
    The subsequent steps to schedule for the TNPSC Group 1 exam is agreed  below:</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <ul>
    <li>The       TNPSC Group 1 application is an online application process. The aspirants       go to the official website of the <a href="https://www.tnpsc.gov.in/">TNPSC - Tamil Nadu Public Service       Commission</a>  www.tnpsc.gov.in. </li>
    <li>Before       that aspirants should read the notification for applying to any of the       posts on the TNPSC website, which implies you to complete One Time       Registration [OTR]. The one-time fee is Rupees 150. Once the aspirants have       made registration on OTR, it is valid for 5 years.</li>
    <li>Applicants       are not required to pay the fee again.</li>
    <li>Before       making one-time registration applicants must have Scanned images of their       recent Photograph, Signature, and require Certificate.</li>
    <li>Candidates       who have already done OTR can use their login ID and password to log into       their TNPSC account to create their dashboard. Candidates cannot create       more than one Registration ID in the OTR.</li>
    <li>Please       note that OTR and OTR is not an       application for any post it is merely just a way to collect necessary       information from applicants and provide the dashboard.</li>
  </ul>
