  <p><h3>TNPSC Group 1 2021 Salary</h3><br>
    The TNPSC Group 1 exam 2021 provides decent payment for all  category posts. Along with the great initial pay scale, they also offer a lot  of benefits and more allowances. The initial pay scale for posts in TNPSC Group  1 2021 is approximately around INR 56100. As mentioned in the TNPSC Group 1  2021 revised, the level of pay is 22 and the payment range is from INR 56100 to  INR 177500. This salary includes base salary and other allowances. Few allowances  offered for TNPSC Group 1(Combined Civil Service) posts are Medical Allowance,  City Compensation Allowance, HRA, and other allowances. These repayment and  allowances may differ from post to post.<br>
  <strong>TNPSC Group 1 2021 Exam Pattern</strong><br>
    TNPSC Group 1 is consists of three exams namely Preliminary  Exam, Mains Exam, and Interview. TNPSC Group 1 2021 Preliminary Exam exists  purely for an initial evaluation. The marks obtain in this first round theory  test do not count towards the last assortment process in TNPSC Group 1 2021.  The common study division of TNPSC Group 1 2021 beginning Examination and TNPSC  Group 1 2021 Mains Examination will have questions in both English and Tamil.<br>
  <strong>TNPSC Group 1 2021 Preliminary Exam</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>TNPSC       Group 1 2021 Prelims exam is fully based on objective type. It has only       one paper consisting of two sections as General Studies Section and the Aptitude       and Mental Ability Test Section.</li>
    <li>The       General Studies section in the TNPSC Group 1 Prelims Exam is in Degree       Standard. It contains 150 questions in total. The Aptitude and Mental       Ability section are of SSLC Standard and it is made up of 50 questions.</li>
    <li>There       are a total of 200 questions in the TNPSC Group 1 2021 beginning exam.</li>
    <li>least       amount qualifying marks for candidates belonging to ST, SC/SC [A], MBC/DC,       BC [OBC], and BCM are 90. For candidate who belong to the “other” group,       it is 120. But the Cut off range will be different.</li>
  </ul>
