  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p><strong>Frequently Asked Questions? (FAQ)</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>1. I’m from Kerala,  Shall I apply for the Group 1 Combined Civil Services Exams?</strong></li>
  </ul>
  <p>For TNPSC Group Exam posting the Tamil Language  is mandatory. If you have adequate knowledge of Tamil you can apply.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>2. Which are Posts comes  under TNPSC Group 1?</strong></li>
  </ul>
  <p>Group-I Services </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Deputy.  Collector </li>
    <li>Deputy.  Superintendent of Police (Category–I) </li>
    <li>Dt.  Registrar, Registration Department </li>
    <li>Asst.  Director of Rural Development Department (Panchayat) / Personal Asst.  (Development) to Collector </li>
    <li>Dt.  Employment Officer </li>
    <li>Divisional  Officer in Fire &amp; Rescue Services </li>
    <li>Asst.  Commissioner (C.T.) </li>
    <li>Deputy.  Registrar of Co-operative Societies 2 </li>
  </ul>
  <p>Group  I A Services<br>
    Asst. Conservator of Forests <br>
    Group I B Service<br>
    Asst. Commissioner, H.R. &amp; C.E <br>
    Group I C Services <br>
    Dt. Educational Officer </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>3. Is there any negative  mark for every wrong answer in the TNPSC exam?</strong></li>
  </ul>
  <p>No, there is no negative for wrong answers.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>4. How many times will I  apply for the TNPSC exam?</strong></li>
  </ul>
  <p>There is a no counting limit for TNPSC Exam; If  you having all eligibility then you can write TNPSC Exam. </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>5. Physical Fitness is  compulsory for all posts of TNPSC Group 1?</strong></li>
  </ul>
  <p>No, Physical Fitness is not compulsory for all  post but following two posts needs the&nbsp;bodily  fitness <br>
    Deputy  Superintendent of Police,<br>
    District  Officer (Fire and Rescue).</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>6. I complete my degree  and my SSLC mark is 305. My SSLC mark is to be considering for TNPSC Exams?</strong></li>
  </ul>
  <p>Your academic mark doesn’t consider for TNPSC  exams. </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>7. While applying TNPSC  Group 1 exam, is there any need to register OTR (one-time Registration) every  time?</strong></li>
  </ul>
  <p>No, once you register for OTR you can use the  same OTR for all TNPSC Exams, but you should renewal. The renewal period  depends according to your community category.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>8. I forget my OTR  Number can I retrieve my OTR number? Or else register again?</strong></li>
  </ul>
  <p>No need to register for register again. You can  retrieve by clicking Forget user Id then give SSLC reg. number and date of  birth you will receive your ID by mail and mobile number.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>9. TNPSC Group 1 Exam posts  are direct posts or not?</strong></li>
  </ul>
  <p>TNPSC Group 1 Exam contains three stages for  selection</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Preliminary Exam(objective type)</li>
    <li>Mains Exam(descriptive type)</li>
    <li>Interview(oral)</li>
  </ul>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>10. For how many years OTR is Valid?</strong></li>
  </ul>
  <p>The validity of the  One Time Registration number is five years. The registered details of One Time  Registration in the TNPSC Portal were available for 5 years and it can be used  to apply for all kinds of TNPSC Group Exams.</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
